animal.description:
Hi! My name is Asa! Sitting in the shelter is no fun, and MVPC knew I was a nice guy, so I came to rescue! 

I am an easy going dog. Walk? Let’s go, I am good on a leash! Snuggle on the couch for a movie? I am game for that too. I am perfectly content to play in the backyard, then come in to chew on a bone. I like kids and adults alike and am pretty independent, so not always in your face. I absolutely want to be with you, but I know when it’s time to lie and watch. I am selective on my dog friends, and cats can be too fun to chase. Did you know they are fun to chase? Overall, I am a good boy hoping to finally land in a family that will love me forever. 

ADOPTION FEE: $200 (All MVPC dogs are heartworm-tested, completely vetted, spayed/neutered, microchipped, crate-trained and house-trained)
ADOPTER: Must have breed experience
BIRTHDAY: Estimated 2 years
FENCE: Required (an electric fence is not an acceptable form of containment)
DOGS: Would prefer to be the only dog
CATS: No, I like to focus on them every once in awhile
CHILDREN: Yes, over 8 please

INQUIRIES: ALL inquiries begin with a submitted adoption application, which is found on our website, www.miamivalleypitcrew.com. We do not adopt to individuals under the age of 25. We prefer male/female dog pairings unless both already reside in the home. 

DO NOT: USE THE PETFINDER CONTACT/ADOPT BUTTONS--we are unable to monitor those and you will not receive a response. 

PLEASE NOTE: We are volunteer based and a home visit is required; we have a two-hour adoption radius from Kettering, OH for our adult dogs and 75 miles for our puppies. Exceptions for our ADULT dogs only, though rare, may be made on a case-by-case basis but we must be able to do a home visit. Thank you for your understanding!

Professional holiday and Valentine’s Day pictures courtesy of the talented Gwen Estep Photography, LLC https://www.facebook.com/GwenEstepPhotography/

animal.description:
There's much that we don't know about beautiful little Beatrice. We don't know how old she is, but she's estimated to be at least 15. We don't know her story because she was a stray picked up by animal control. However there's much more that we do know about this 8-lb Rat Terrier with the low-ridin' look of a Teddy, or Type B, Rat Terrier. We know that her teeth used to be in wretched condition and caused her great pain. Now that all but the two lower canines have been removed, Beatrice feels ever so much better. We know that she's in remarkably good health and has no conditions that require meds. While she's past her playful stage, she gets along nicely with other dogs and cats. She earned the name Beatrice because of her love of skittering about like a busy bee. She doesn't like to be held, but we know she loves to snuggle. She also likes to be fed her by hand. She eats better that way, and we know you'll enjoy the bonding experience as much as she does. Beatrice isn't house-trained, but we know she'll do her best if you're vigilant and offer her frequent opportunities to go outside to potty. There's one more thing we know about this sweetheart--Beatrice believes there's somebody who can't wait to make her golden years the very best! So be that somebody! We know that you won't regret it.
Our adoption fee is $175 for adult dogs or $225 for puppies under 6 months old.

If you are interested in adopting this dog,
PLEASE READ THE DETAILED ADOPTION PROCESS information on our website
at www.
NewRattitude.org/adopt/

From there, you can access our adoption application or contact our Adoption Team for more info.

animal.description:
Hi! I am HANK THE TANK! I am an 8-year-old, 72-pound, bundle of love! I love food, I love sleeping and I love toys, I love my foster mom and dad, I love kids, I love walks, I love treats, I love car rides, and oh yeah, I love other dogs. I just LOVE life!

Are you looking for a pup to enjoy life with? If so, that would be me!!

The first 8 years of my life were bad. My tongue has a cut on it, many of my teeth have fallen out, and I have scars on my ears. I was skin and bones when a nice lady saved me. Now, I am looking for a furever home where I will be loved and spoiled.

Even though I've had a rough life, I still have a loving heart. My foster family tells me I'm pretty amazing, since I was betrayed by humans, but can still show tremendous love for them. I need someone that will kiss my lovey, smooshy face each day and remind me that I am loved.

I am house trained and crate trained. I like my crate for those times when you leave the house.

I am good on a leash and I don't even pull. I get really excited when it's time for my walk!

Here's a list of what I am looking for in my furever family:
1. Someone home most of the day.

2. A

home that understands a typical lab's goofy personality!

3. A fenced yard where I can lounge and chase squirrels.

4. Someone that likes to take daily walks.
5. Maybe even another doggie sibling to play with.

So who's ready to be my furever family and love life with me?!

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online. http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

Please be sure to like our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/angelsrescue.

Meet Miller Kyle. Miller is 2+year-old, Scooby-Doo lookalike weighing in at about 66-pounds

We have Miller Kyle listed as a Pit Bull/Labrador mix (

maybe some SharPei?) but he sure looks a lot like Scooby-Doo.

This sweet guy is a perfect house-guest who wants to move into your home and be your one and only full-time companion.

Miller Kyle loves playing frisbee, going on walks, running, car rides and snuggle time. He is also house and crate trained but really enjoys sleeping with his humans. Miller Kyle likes to chill in the crate on his own when he's home alone, but you don't have to worry about leaving him out of his crate when you're gone - he's very respectful of house items and even human food. But Miller Kyle isn't a fan of other dog.

This super-smart guy knows commands like, "sit," "down," "touch," "go say hi," and he is mastering "place" meaning he goes to lay on his dog bed. He very much enjoys training, and he will work for treats!

Miller Kyle also enjoys solving the mysteries of the back yard, like where did the squirrel hide his nuts, what is the large-4-legged, furry thing with horns. Who knows, maybe Miller Kyle can help you solve crimes?

animal.description:
ROSA

Rosa is a 7-8-year-old bloodhound who came to us from a shelter in Texas. She is a classic bloodhound, sweet and stubborn, loving to her people, good with other dogs, although she seems to prefer the males over the female in her foster home. Considering where she is from, there was no surprise that she was heartworm positive. She has been treated, and has no residual effects, but she will require some follow up on the part of her adopter. She is crate trained and house trained with a dog door. Good with small dogs, but cats are unknown. She has not met kids that we know of, but we suspect she would be fine with kids 8 and up. She tends to put her paws up on her person as if to hug them and this might be a bit much for a young child.  Leash skills are so-so as she does pull somewhat. 

Rosa’s adoption fee is $225. If you are interested in adopting her, please fill out an application on our web site: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1SnhudHYFJaPfZyCeKy36-9pbowOVOI-xrX4TIiSIxl4/edit and a volunteer will contact you about a home visit

We URGENTLY need fosters so we can help save more dogs.  If you can help, please contact us.

animal.description:
Meet Johnny, a handsome dazzler looking for a specific home and sidekick, that will be able to provide the structure and management he needs to be set up for success. Johnny has some training under his belt like being potty trained, basic commands, and muzzle trained but will need more work in his adoptive home. Best Friends is offering FREE training sessions to help him get on the right routine and training plan to ensure he makes good life choices! Johnny requires an in-person Lifesaving Center Visit and counseling. 

 Johnny is a staff favorite for so many reasons, but his smile, sweet nose freckles, and tail wiggles help brighten anyone's day. While Johnny has a loving and loyal personality with the people he has bonded with, he is a work in progress and requires an adult only home (18 years and older) where he will be the only animal. Due to his stressors caused by previous negative experiences, his next home must be aware that he needs to be cautiously managed when around high populations of people OR other animals and is not a candidate for any off-leashing activities. He thrives with structure and routine and will need to continue these habits in his new home. If you are interested in learning more about Johnny and setting up an interview for an in person meet and greet, email utahadoptions@bestfriends.org

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

UPDATE: Remi needs to go to a Northern dog experienced home with at least one other dog.

---

Remi is a VERY sweet Malamute/Husky/German Shepard/White Swiss Shepard mix (DNA results). He's 2 years old and a big boy of 80 pounds. He's potty trained and walks nicely on a leash without pulling. He's submissive with other dogs and people and hesitant with men. Remi is gentle and very sensitive. He wants to please more than anything in this world. Remi does not play with toys right now but he LOVES any game of chase and he will snatch something of value, a sock, a shirt . . . to get you to chase him. Adorable!

Remi was found as a stray in Oakland and then adopted straight from the shelter. His inexperienced new owner returned him after just 4 days for separation anxiety.

Despite having 4 other dogs to be around at his NorSled foster home, Remi still has very pronounced separation anxiety. We are working on this issue but we like to be transparent to potential adopters. (If you have leather furniture, Remi may not be the dog for you.)

If you have other Northern dogs and have the patience and desire to help Remi resolve his separation anxiety, please submit an application
www.norsled.org.
Thank you. Remi is being fostered in Oakland.

Shiloh may have injuries to the muscles, tendons, etc. that are still healing. There is visible atrophy of the left rear thigh/leg muscles at the time of the exam. Temperament: Shiloh is a well behaved, affectionate, and obedient indoor dog. He is very smart and agile and, therefore, should always be considered a flight risk pet. He knows how to open doors with level style handles, push sliding doors open (including "doggy doors"), and use yard objects as stepping stones to leap over 6' fences.

Super sweet dog and would make a great companion or walking partner. --

animal.description:
Please fill out the application now if you are interested as we are still closed to the public and doing meet & greets and adoptions by appointment only.

Pablo is so much fun! If you are looking for a long, lanky boy to play with, then Pablo is your guy.  He was born in August 2015 and weighs 66 pounds but he could probably stand to gain a few extra pounds. Our best guess is that he’s a Rottweiler/Catahoula/Doberman on stilts. He’s the true definition of a “Heinz 57” dog; he’s just a little bit of everything. This year has been hard on everyone, including Pablo, whose owner could no longer afford him and had to surrender him to McKamey. We decided to help him out and give him a change of scenery here at PPC. He’s extremely smart, potty trained, and friendly with everyone. He already knows a few commands including “sit” and “down," and he’s learning “lay down.” He’s an active boy who loves to play and gets along with every dog he meets, however, he’s a little too rough with cats, so ideally he needs to be in a home with only canine companions. His favorite activities include playing fetch (poorly), cuddling, and napping with his favorite people. You’d be surprised at how much he just wants to be a lap dog. If you want a dog who’s ready to go on adventures and play at the dog park, then give us a call!

Pablo recently went out on another hiking adventure and his handler said this about him: "This fella’s got the most amazing pouty face (when he wants a treat), and is a super nice dog. He will run splendidly right beside you, is only mildy curious when we passed other people/dogs (this is HUGE if you’ve ever owned a reactive pupper) and does not pull on a leash. He’s so treat motivated. I swear to dog he reminds me of an AT-AT Walker (I had to google ‘Star Wars long legged machine thingy’). Pablo is a funny dude!"

We're open Wednesday - Sunday 12 - 5 p.m but are doing meet & greets and adoptions by appointment only.  

The adoption fee is $90 which includes a free veterinary exam within 2 weeks of adoption at local participating vets, up to date vaccinations, heartworm test,  heartworm preventative, dewormer, flea preventative, microchip, & spay or neuter.

If you are interested in this pet, please fill out our ADOPTION APPLICATION at https://goo.gl/forms/9FdDBiPU5aa5ySTv1

Visit our website at www.PetPlacementCenter.com

To be considered for adopting a dog from Canine Lifeline, you must have an approved application must be on file. Please visit http://www.caninelifeline.org/adoption-process/ for more information about our adoption process and to submit an online application.

Stormy is a bright-eyed and alert 3 year-old Terrier mix spayed female with a beautiful dark brown coat who found herself shelter bound after her owner died and no one in her extended family could take her on. She was understandably stressed and confused at having lost the only home she'd ever known so made the trip to Canine Lifeline so she could take her time finding a new forever home. We don't know anything about Stormy's previous life although it was likely that she was the only dog in her home. While she has done well with the other dogs in her foster home, we think she would probably enjoy having her new humans all to herself and not have to share them with another dog. Stormy has had excellent crate manners in her foster home and may be housetrained too although we can't guarantee that. She is quite strong on a leash for a smaller-sized dog and would do well with an Easy Walk Harness as she works on her leash manners. With some daily practice, she will soon be walking like a pro and make a great walking or hiking buddy for someone looking for a smaller yet very spunky companion who can definitely keep up with the big dogs. Stormy weighs about 26 pounds and her adoption fee is $325. She's spayed, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. Please email info@caninelifeline.org if you're interested in Stormy. An approved application is required before we schedule meets with any of our dogs. Please note that we don't place our dogs in homes with children under 7 years of age. We correspond via email so please check your junkmail or spam folder to make sure our reply hasn't landed in there. Please visit our website at www.caninelifeline.org to see more photos of Stormy and to submit an online application if you live in Northeast OH.

Maya is a shy but sweet 3 year-old Lab mix female who looks like she might have had a rough life in the past. She was found as a stray and when she wasn't claimed at the local county dog shelter, made the trip to Canine Lifeline so she could relax in a foster home while searching for a permanent new home. Maya was initially very shy and nervous when she came to us and will likely be timid when meeting new people. It does take her some time to trust someone new so her new family must be patient with her as she gets used to her new environment. Maya is very comfortable around other dogs and loves playing chase and wrestling with her canine buddies in her foster home. She would do best in a home where she'll have a canine pal to show her the ropes and help boost her confidence. Given her shyness, she will need a home with a yard that has a secure aboveground fence. She would not be comfortable in a busy urban or suburban environment so is looking for a home in a very quiet neighborhood or rural area. Maya has had excellent crate manners in her foster home so may be housetrained too although we can't guarantee it. She will need some work on a leash and will do best walking with a harness as she works on her leash skills. Maya weighs about 44 pounds and her adoption fee is $325. She's spayed, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. It takes her time to warm up to men as she is afraid of them. She is three years old and spends a lot of time relaxing now after what must have been a crazy life for this little lady. She does enjoy walks and is responding well to leash training and any training we try. Cherokee Rose has a fear of kennels, but has made herself a safe space on our couch, where she likes to hang out as well as sleep. She's come out of her shell since being here with us especially since we have a resident dog who she follows everywhere. We think it's essential she be in a home with other dogs because she's really done well here with a buddy and I think she'd be pretty lost alone. Cherokee doesn't really "play" as she is way too serious for that, but does enjoy the company of the resident pup. She's not been around cats so not sure how that will go. She's recently finished heartworm treatment and is ready for her forever home. She's really a sweet girl who just wants to be petted and loved. She'll make a great addition to a family with patience and love to give her.

animal.description:
**PLEASE READ THIS BIO IN IT'S ENTIRETY BEFORE REACHING OUT!!**

Meet Zelda! 

We scooped her up juuuuuuuust before Hurricane Zeta hit. She was emaciated, running around Central City, New Orleans. She was surely once someone's good girl. She's impeccably trained - knows sit, paw, other paw, down and even runs into her kennel when her meals are being prepped. She's good with men, women and other dogs. I'm going to assume cats are a no go. She LOVES destroying stuffed animals - the squeaker is her prize. She loves cozy dog beds and loafing around on a good couch. She'll lay her big fat head on you and melt you with those big brown eyes. If we had room for one more, we'd keep her without hesitation. If I was still a single woman living in the city, THIS gal would be my best friend and best home defense system. 

She is about 4 years old, spayed UTD on all vaccinations and currently undergoing heartworm treatment, which we will fully fund. She's put a good deal of meat back on her bones and is well on her way to being healthy again. We anticipate her to max out at about 70#.  Her activity will need to be limited while she undergoes HW treatment. She does exceptionally well in a kennel, so this should be easy peasy. 

Her ideal home are seasoned bully-breed owners without small children. Although she is well-trained, she is a VERY STRONG animal. She usually takes treats from your hand with care, but there are definitely times she does not. She usually grabs just the toy from your hand when playing, but there's definitely times she inadvertently snags your finger. For those reasons, we'd like to keep children out of the equation. 

If you think you are a good fit for Zelda, Please fill out an application for consideration.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*We are NOT a shelter. We are a foster-based rescue with NO facility. PLEASE take a moment to read more about who we are and what we do at Trampled Rose Rescue & Rehab HERE: 

https://www.petfinder.com/member/us/la/ponchatoula/trampled-rose-rescue-rehab-la410/   

It outlines, in great detail, our adoption process, adoption fees, how we select forever homes and much more.

*If you think you may be a good fit for one of our rescue dogs, PLEASE SUBMIT AN APPLICATION for consideration. Feel free to drop a line with any questions we haven't answered, however, ONLY SUBMITTED APPLICATIONS WILL BE CONSIDERED AND PROCESSED. 

*If the dog is visible to you here on Petfinder, IT IS STILL AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION, so NO NEED TO ASK. The moment a home visit agreement is signed, the dog will be marked 'Adoption Pending' and, if all goes well, 'Adopted'. If the home visit was not a success, the dog will be relisted as 'Adoptable'. 

*We get DOZENS (and sometimes HUNDREDS) of messages via Petfinder, Instagram, Facebook, Twitter, phone, text and email about EACH of our rescues DAILY. We do the best we can to respond to them all, but ultimately there's just not enough hours in the day. If you're seriously interested in a dog, the best course of action is to submit an application and BE PATIENT. We DO go through EVERY application that we receive, on a first come first served basis, and will select the home BEST SUITED for that particular rescue. We almost exclusively deal with special needs dogs and there is an ideal lifestyle we have in mind for each of our rescues. If you DO NOT receive a call it DOES NOT mean you were forgotten or declined. We likely had a barrage of applicants before you and one of those was a clear winner. Please keep in mind, we all have full time jobs, families and fosters and permanent pets of our own, so PLEASE be patient and allow us ample time to do this volunteer work in what little free time we have. Thank you.

*Applications are available on our main page here on Petfinder OR on our website, www.trampledroserescue.com/adopt. Thnx!

animal.description: I'm Dodger (HWTH#20275A)!  I am a German Shepherd, born on 11/14/14 and I weigh 60 lbs.  I arrived at Halfway to Home after I was found by a Good Samaritan as a stray dragging a leash near the aqueduct in Lake Los Angeles.   My owner never claimed me so now I am looking for a forever family!  I am truly "man's best friend" as I seem to be drawn to men in particular, however I am friendly with all the adults I have met.  I am not sure if I get along with kids or other dogs. I love balls and other squeaky toys.  I am a strong and high-energy boy, therefore obedience training is essential to ensure I learn how to walk on a leash without pulling and what is acceptable behavior.  Apartments, condos, or mobile homes would not be suitable for me because I need a large fenced yard to exercise and play.   I need at least 2 long walks a day, and I would love to be a jogging or hiking partner.  When we aren't participating in outdoor activities,  I want to be an indoor dog and treated as a member of your family.   If you like what you have read and you would like more information or an appointment to meet me, please call Sandy at tele#661-824-4495 (this is a landline).  Thank you!

animal.description:
Don't miss out on Chance by emailing us to see if he is still available.??
Check the Photo Gallery on our website and see if they are marked PENDING OR ADOPTED.
APPLY if interested so you can be considered.
When he is adopted or pending, we put it on the gallery photo of our home page.

PLEASE check our website Daily for any updates.  www.wowdogrescue.org 
*Our page is updated daily. Please go to www.wowdogrescue.org for any updates.

Chance is a mix of Pomeranian and Maltese we think..
He is a tiny little guy weighing approx. 8 lbs.
He can get through the tiniest places, and is terribly missing his deceased owner of 10 yrs.
He would be happy to live with another male, and him being the one and only...like he is used too. He is not aggressive with other dogs, but enjoys getting all the attention. 

Right now he is with a male foster, and has done well with his 2 small dogs. He doesn't interact with them, and doesn't try to play with them at all.
Chance is a nervous little guy at first, but he will settle in nicely after he knows he is safe and loved.
He will sit next to the foster on his legs while on his chair now, so is feeling pretty comfortable there.
If you are looking for a sweet boy who LOVES going for walks and having a back yard to run around in...he's your boy! APPLY!

Chance is WAS scheduled to be neutered and get his microchip, and Rabies
shot BUT he is no longer a candidate to have this done as he gets very anxious and the vet felt is is in his best interest not to have the surgery.

He is current on his Rabies, DHPP and Bordetella. He also has his microchip inserted.
He is ready for his forever home now. 

Chances adoption fee is $175.00 UNLESS you are a senior..  then his adoption fee is $100.00 plus anything the rescue has in to him but not to exceed $175.00

We are NOT Petfinder, 
We are not Adoptapet,
OR
Rescue me.

Our application is on OUR website:  www.wowdogrescue.org 

**PLEASE do not call to see if he is "still" available.
His Gallery photo on our website will be updated daily and will state his status.
IF we have chosen someone, he will be marked "Pending".
IF he has been adopted, he will be marked "Adopted".

***Tired of not finding, or not being chosen for the dog of your dream??
Consider Fostering with us...Our Fosters have 1st chance at adopting the dog they foster, while we pay for everything.
Its a win win for both! YOU get to see if this is a good match for your family, while the dog is being loved in your home...

animal.description: Hi! My name is Lucy and I am an American Bulldog (Scott Line). I was brought to the local animal shelter as a stray in Sept. and no one claimed me. I was so sad and distraught that I began to lose weight. A local rescue group saw how well I behaved and felt sorry for me. They placed me with their dog trainer who agreed that I was a good girl. One of the volunteers offered to foster me in her home and I felt so much more at ease. I am eating well now and enjoy going for walks. My foster home has cats and I do not mind them at all. The vet thinks I am a senior but I feel young and enjoy playing in the yard. I would LOVE to find a permanent home to call my own. Maybe you are the one I've been waiting for? Please call (631) 219-8529 and ask about me. I'll be waiting!

animal.description:
Please only send inquires to the email in this bio all others will not be answered. Please read the bio before sending questions - we answer all we know about the dog here.

Hello everyone- my name is Milo! I'm about 3 years old with the most precious heart. My previous owner was in the military and because of their offshore duties, I had to be surrendered. I loooove to play with any kinds of toys, I love long walks, and when I'm excited I hop around, and that's how I landed the nickname bugs bunny! When we're done playing, I hope you're ready for cuddles! I am so sweet and talkative, and I'm ready for a human to call my own. I would do well as the only dog in a home, but if I meet my possible sibling and we get along, that works just as well. I am house trained, but may need some time to adjust to your schedule so I don't have an accident. (I usually bark if I have to go)

Milo's adoption fee is $300 - Obedience training is required after adoption Obedience training is also required for all our pups.

Obedience training is also required for all our pups. We understand with what is going on in the world that this may be a bit delayed. Please email us the completion certificate.

To apply to foster or adopt please fill out application at

www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

Thank you for completing the application. We are all volunteers and short on time, we will contact you back only if we have more questions or your application is approved and you will be invited to meet the dog. We apologize for not being able to answer everyone back.

For more information contact Kelly.V@HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

DOGS are in Foster Homes. There is NO shelter.

**Our companions MUST live in your home as part of your family.**We do not transport.

**See our website for more information. www.HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

All communication is thru email so please be patient with us. We are all volunteers and work full time jobs and have families of our own.

It takes anywhere between 3-7 days to process an application - the more complete the application the easier it is for us to process it. Please notify your vet that we will be contacting them and to release information to us.

ADOPTION PROCESS:

1. Complete this application
www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

***Everyone must submit an application - we only keep them on file for 1 month

2. Application background check, vet check, etc

3. Invitation thru email to meet the dog(s).

4. Adoption Contract

animal.description:
Say hi to Smokey. He 's a 40lbs hound/sharpei mix. He was relinquished to Hawaii Dog Foundation due to a worsening skin infection. 

We took him directly to the vet to get a better understanding of his health status.  Smokey was diagnosed with demodectic mange and hookworm.  He was immediately given medicine for the hookworm and a flea & tick preventative to address the mange.  Frequent baths, good food and continued care should get his skin feeling better in no time. 

Smokey is a vert gentle boy. He really does just want human care and attention. Smokey does very well with other dogs, but we've not seen him with cats just yet. 

He is not quite ready for adoption right now (Nov 2020), but we suspect by Christmas or the new year, he'll be feeling much better.

If you'd like to meet Smokey, please complete an adoption application on our website, www.hawaiidogfoundation.org and ask for him by name. We'll give yo a call t set something up!

animal.description:
Our sweet girl Aristotle has been to our last two adoption events. She was such a good girl at both events. So good that she even got to ride shotgun on the way back to the shelter! 

Two times in a row Aristotle rode shotgun while the other crates in the van were empty. She was the only dog not adopted at BOTH events ? 

In fact, this amazingly sweet and gentle girl has been with us since October and we're not sure why she keeps getting overlooked.

Aristotle is a 3 1/2 year old Pitbull mix with the sweetest disposition. She is a petite girl weighing only 40 pounds. If you're looking for a calm and laid back dog- she is the one for you! She doesn't require a lot of exercise, but does require a lot of love! Aristotle does well around other calm and well mannered dogs but she does not like playful or high energy dogs. Because of this she needs a meet and greet before going home. (no kitties). She is kid friendly and loves car rides too!

Adoption fee is 125.00 which includes spay, vaccines, and microchip.

If you want to give Aristotle the chance she's been patiently waiting for, come on in Tues-Sun 11am-3pm to meet her!
www.JARMission.org/adopt
843-726-7799

animal.description:
Sir Philip was knighted on 24 Oct 2020. ? He was rescued from a homeless camp on the west side of the island of Oahu. 

Some of his royal demands thus far...
4 meals a day ? 
Soft spot to rest his head
Treats on commands ? 
Scratches whenever 
Rocked to sleep ?

As you can see, Sir Philip needs some work on his noble demands.

Phil came to us malnourished at 23lbs. As of Thanksgiving, 2020, he's up to 30 lbs. We think he'd be at ideal weight at 35lbs. So, he needs to gain a wee bit more weight before he is neutered and microchipped.  We've learned that he is a lover and not a fighter. He wants nothing more than to be with the human that has the food and will give him belly rubs. We think he'd do best in a home without small children, but definitely another dog to help him continue to come out of his shell. 

If you'd like to meet this shy, but loving guy, please complete an adoption application on our website, wwwmhawaiidogfoundation.org and ask for him by name.

animal.description:
Chachi is a 4 to 5 year old female Hound/Shepherd mix weighing 54 pounds. She sports a tricolor, medium length coat, and her eyes are deep and tell her story. Chachi's owner could no longer afford to keep her and, as a result, Chachi's life changed dramatically. Now she's a dog in need of consistency to feel secure. She's an emotionally fragile dog who is playful and energetic but also worried when she meets strangers. She's quite intelligent, but also petrified of the vet. She has lived with another dog, and yet she doesn't like other dogs living in the same home, and she will not live with cats or small children. She will walk with another dog, but she must know the dog first. She loves toys and must have a fenced in yard to help her with her high energy. Are you a person with experience with dogs, who understands dogs, and who is willing to spend time reassuring this dog that she is loved and will never be given up again? We mean this. She's wonderful girl who has been dealt a life of uncertainty. She needs you. In-depth conversation with her foster will help both you and the foster decide if the adoption would be good for you and for Chachi. (posted 9/4/20, HS) (revised 10/13/20) (revised 12/26/20, HS)
**It is rare that we know with certainty the ages or mixes that make up our dogs, but we do our best to be as accurate as possible based upon our experience.
Adoption: $225.00The total fee for Chachi, which includes adoption and transport, is only $225.00. This is not because there is anything wrong with her; we just want her in your home as soon as possible.

animal.description:
IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING SNOOKIE, PLEASE GO TO THE MAKE A DIFFERENCE RESCUE FACEBOOK PAGE AND SEND A PRIVATE MESSAGE THAT INCLUDES YOUR PHONE NUMBER AND EMAIL ADDRESS.

Beautiful Snookie is an 10 year old Terrier mix who's family took her to the vet to be euthanized because a baby was coming. The vet contacted Make A Difference Rescue to see if we could take her in. Of course, we said YES!! Snookie is an amazing girl!!  She loves to be around people, loves warm & cozy dog beds and most of all she loves to be loved on. Snookie is good with other  dogs after a proper introduction is done. Unfortunately, we do not know how she is with cats. Snookie needs a fenced in yard where she can safely run and play. Children 12 years or older. Snookie is up to date on her vaccinations, on heartworm preventative as well as house and crate trained. Snookie is scheduled to be spayed. Snookie cannot wait to be part of a loving family who will cherish and spoil her for the rest of her life.

All dogs we rescue stay with us until they find their forever homes. We do not do same day adoptions. A home visit is required to ensure our dog is going to a safe environment and our dog gets along with your dog(s) and/or cat(s). We require all our dogs over the age of 1 year attend 1 obedience class (6 week session) outside the home. You must live within 1 hour of Birmingham, MI to adopt one of our dogs. No out of state or outside the U.S. adoptions or fosters. Snookie's adoption fee is $275.

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Shanti, I'm a DEAF heeler, 38 lbs, socially awkward, and a ball of loving, furry energy! I'm looking for my very own special person/people because as I've matured into a young lady, I can no longer live with canine sisters. I'm a very good girl, I know my basic dog commands and other commands via hand signal, I love nose work and long-line work. I even volunteer for my city's geese management program using a muzzle and long-line (due to breed tendencies and being deaf) and with mom of course. I know all about using a dog door, crate, halter, gentle leader, and muzzle. I'm house trained and even know to ring a bell if the dog door is closed and I need to go out to do my business. I know to feel for floor vibrations or look at a flashlight as a "look at me" signal when inside. I love car rides and new adventures! I need daily exercise and mental stimulation to release some of my natural heeler energy otherwise I can get myself into trouble when I create my own kind of fun. I really, really need someone who knows and loves everything about hard-wired working heelers 'cause we're pretty special and not everybody's cup of tea. So if you know all about heelers then you just have learn my deaf hand signals and I can learn about you-perfect match! I also need someone who is home a lot because I'm what's known as a "Velcro" dog due to my breed type and deafness-I need, need my people and would be very stressed if you're gone a lot of time so it would be a very sad life for me. I currently eat a raw diet (mom says it's to keep my protein high and carbs low). I love back rubs and neck massages-this helps me relax! Unlike most heelers I do have a tendency to be relatively verbal (my way of connecting to the world since I'm deaf) -I like to grumble at things I see out the window, or make self-soothing sounds. All in all, I'm a pretty resilient lil gal looking for my very own person/people! Here's more info from mom:

Shanti Needs:

 Best to be the only dog but could possibly live with an older, larger, gentle, very calm male dog (would need gentle and gradual introductions)

 Yard with a secure 6 ft fence, no apartments

 Daily physical activity: walking or running at least 30-45 minutes daily, ideally two times per day or other activities and access to yard

 A loving person who can be her leader

 A person experienced as a dog guardian and ideally experience with heelers

 No children, no cats, no small animals (due to strong breed tendencies)

 Willing to learn hand signals and continue training to help her be a full member of the family

 Person/people who can be with her the majority of time

 Person to keep her on leash, watch for door dashing and be aware of dangers for a deaf dog

Her adoption fee is $250. Submit an app at www.eapl.com

Meet Zoey...
Zoe is deaf. And while this does not define her or slow her down she will need someone who is willing to make the extra effort and learn to communicate with her using hand signals. She is eager to please and loves nothing more than playing fetch with her favorite ball before cuddling with her humans. 

Zoe will do best with someone who is home a lot and has time to spend with her as she really likes human companionship. This beautiful girl was found running around the streets all alone. She had been thrown away like trash after giving birth. How scared she must have been. Immediately after rescue we found out she needed emergency surgery as she had an infection in her uterus. We are happy to say she is doing great today and all healed. Zoe is an extra special girl who has plenty of love to give. 

We are looking for a foster hero in the NYC/NJ who can open their heart and home to this beautiful soul. Please apply at zionsmission.org

"We must dare to be great..." and together we shall be!  My name is Teddy Roosevelt.  I've spent the last 4 years of my life preparing, studying, and dreaming for my future role as your newly appointed Forever Love!  I know this is my chance to really make a difference in the world and I am the man for the job!  I am an 85lb., lab mix hunk of handsome.  I am a studious fella and a quick study.  I have already mastered house training and crate training.  I know how to "sit" and "shake" when asked politely.  I know how to read my humans and will adapt to whatever they are doing! I adore being with my humans.  I am not so keen on those male dogs or cats, but hey, those lady doggos are delightful.  I also like kids; they are pretty fun.  I am looking for a presidential residence where the two of us can enjoy our days together and play out in our privacy fenced backyard.  I definitely need a privacy fenced yard and do not want to live in any apartments.  I think the two of us could be a duo for the history books!  They'll carve our story into rock and tell tales of our amazing adventures!  Now "keep your eyes on the stars and your feet on the ground" and fill out my adoption application so we can start our historic forever friendship!


My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.special_needs_notes:
Blue has a condition called Mega E or megaesophagus. Megaesophagus is a condition in which the muscles of the esophagus lose their tone and are no longer able to propel food into the stomach. In normal function wave like contractions move the food from the mouth to the stomach. When megaesophagus occurs the esophagus dilates, or enlarges, due to lack of muscle tone. This causes the food to just sit in the esophagus, unable to continue into the stomach to get digested. 
Blue is a relatively easy keeper. She eats a blend of dry kibble, a can of wet dog food mixed with water to create a soup type of consistency. She eats elevated. We you a coffee table to put her food bowl on and she stands up to reach the bowl. She does not require any special chair.

animal.description:
The only thing "senior" about this guy is the little bit of white on his face!! He's an active, exuberant happy dog that would love an equally active family. About 60 lbs of wiggle butt! He lived his whole 9 years with a family but they moved to a home where they can't have another dog so Nestor finds himself looking for a forever home. He will need a fenced yard so he can run and play safely. He would also love to go hiking, walking or running with his new family.  He currently goes for 2 hour hikes 4 days a week with our volunteers.. Older children would be best for him because his energy level might be too much for small kids- he would knock them over. Nester seems to be way too interested in cats so none of them in the household either. A playful dog his size might be OK but would have to do a meet and greet. Nester is a great snuggle buddy and will hang out with you on the couch after a day hiking. He is totally house trained and good on his own in the house.

Nester is up to date on all his shots, neutered and microchipped. 

We are looking for a home for within an hour's drive of Phillipsburg,  NJ. For more information about Nester, please contact us at grrnewjersey@gmail.com. If you're interested in adopting him, please email us for an adoption application. You can also find us on Facebook (facebook.com/GRRNJ).

animal.description: Aubrey has been at ACSKC since January 2020Aubrey is like a morning spent puttering around the house in pajamas pants as you take your time with that first cup of coffee. During those long, lazy days, Aubrey is the perfect companion. It is easy to picture him padding up alongside you, offering his head for a scratch behind the ears, before laying at your feet.A gentle and laidback Terrier mix, Aubrey has eyes like warm, deeply steeped tea and a terracotta coat with a dusting of white that gives him a distinguished look. Affectionately called The Old Man, Aub is in good health at 9 years old and does not require a lot of exercise. A short stroll a few times a day is all he needs. In fact, hes a bit of a couch potato! Aubrey is one of our long-timers, as he has been at the shelter since January. When he arrived, he began treatment for heartworms and has just recently been declared heartworm-free!While he does not beg for attention, Aub is more than happy to receive pets, and will wait patiently while you get a treat from the cupboard for him. He offers the quiet company that can make any routine day feel comfortable and uncomplicated.Want to meet Aubrey? Head to kenthumane.org to submit an application. Due to COVID-19 precautions, The Animal Care Shelter for Kent County is open by appointment only. Once your application is approved, we will set up an appointment with you!Animal meetings and adoptions by appointment only. Please go to kenthumane.org/adoption-applicationOnce approved we will call you to set up an appointment!

animal.description:
Ehhh, what up, Doc? Oh wait, that's my name! Hey, I'm Doc, a 10-year-old mix breed gentleman here at Stray Haven. You're sure to notice that have a couple bumps on me. Don't worry, I just have a few skin tags, they're no big deal -- I'm an old man! I came here all the way from a high-kill shelter in North Carolina. I'm excited to be here! The sights and smells of a new place were a little overwhelming at first, but I'm starting to get used to life here at Stray Haven. I kind of like to keep to myself. Sometimes new people approaching me can be scary. It took me a second to open up to the caretakers here, but I'm learning that they aren't so bad. I love it when they take me outside! There's a huge yard here that I loooove running around in! I just want to soak it all up! Once I'm inside, I'm a peach. All I need is a nice warm bed and I'm set. I was an owner surrender, so I'm cautious about getting too attached to people, as I am worried they will just leave me. All I need is someone to show me unconditional love, and I'll fill a hole in your heart you never knew you had. It's a very special thing to adopt an old dog like me -- these are my golden years! I keep my kennel very clean. I'm not sure how I would feel about living with cats or other dogs; maybe ask the staff so you can have a conversation. I could probably live with older kids as long as they respect me. I think I need a home where the people love me for who I am and spoil me as I grow old and gray. If you're interested in being my new family, please come meet me at Stray Haven!
Stray Haven Humane Society & SPCA
194 Shepard Rd., Waverly, NY 14892
(607) 565-2859, www.strayhavenspca.org 
Open hours (winter): Tues, Wed & Thurs Noon - 6pm; Sat 10am-4pm

animal.description:
Heyoooo!! My name is Ace, and I'm 2 and a half years old. I'm a happy guy with a TON of energy! My favorite thing in the world is to zoom around the yard as fast as I can! I originally came from North Carolina. I was brought up to New York a while ago to try my luck at finding! Life at Stray Haven is a dream! I get plenty of yard time, and caretakers do such a good job making sure I'm stimulated and having a relaxing stay here at the shelter. They're also teaching me the basics of being a dog. I'm working on my leash manners, and I'll admit, I'm having a hard time. I'm a really smart dog so I definitely have the potential to learn. I can sit like nobody's business, and I love snacks!! I'll literally do anything for a treat! I think I would do best in a home with older kids because I jump and nibble on people occasionally. I shouldn't live with other dogs because I can be a relentless player. Living with cats probably won't work out; they sound like they would be a lot of fun to chase! I definitely need lots of rules along with mental and physical stimulation to keep me happy in my future home. Once I learn some leash manners, long walks would be nice. Until then, I think a fenced in yard is a must for me. If you're interested in seeing my big smiling face, come down to Stray Haven and ask for me, Ace!!

animal.description:
Dudley is  a very affectionate and beautiful dog looking for an active and loving home. He was not given much attention or direction in his first year on this earth but is now in a intense training program where he has learned to not only walk well on a leash, but he is doing pack walks with 8 other dogs. He has integrated into a very large pack and is learning that the world is a fun and safe place. Dudley loves to play and just need a patient and experienced family that will show him how to be a part of a household. He is potty trained as well. I think Dudley would do best with older children because he is playful and may knock over small kids, even though he wouldn't mean to. Dudley comes with a trainer that will show you how to maintain everything he has learned. Dudley is eager to please and treat motivated. 

Dudley is dog friendly and will pair best with a dog who can match his energy and run around and play in the backyard with. 

If you are interested in adopting Dudley or want to see videos of Dudley in action, please reach out.

To apply for adoption: 
https://forgottencoastanimalrescue.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Toto

is a super sweet senior needing a whole lot of love!!!

This poor boy was part of a cruelty case from Barc along with 8 other dogs. We had pulled his brother, Buddy, having been told all others had been saved. Well, the next day, the person who had taken

Toto

returned him due to a cough!!!! Seriously????

As soon as we saw the plea, we knew we could not let this precious boy die alone at Barc, because yet another human had let him down.

Toto

is a pretty simple guy who just wants some love. He loves to sit right next to you with your arm draped around him.

He is estimated to be about 11 years old. He is a cattle dog mix and unfortunately, is heartworm positive, but of course we will take care of that.

Toto

is a great boy who would love a super comfy bed and a reliable human to spend the rest of his life with. Might that be you?

If so please complete our application at
www.scoutshonor.org

animal.description:
Adopt from OPP & save a life... we take unwanted pets from community members on the Pine Ridge Indian Reservation in South Dakota.

Meet Mika, a 3 year old young lady, with German Shepherd  in her ancestry. She was vet checked as are all our in takes and found to be pregnant. Hum we thought it was all the good food she was eating! She had her puppies and all of them will be available for adoption in 2021. Her puppies are now 4 weeks old and will be ready for adoption in a few weeks. There are 6 of them :Art, Cousin Eddie, Ellen, Aunt Bethany, Clark, and Russell. Once the kids are weaned it's  Mika's turn to find a good home where she can be spoiled.

Please contact Andrea @ andrea@oglalapetproject.org for an adoption application. Adoption fee is $200. Adoption applications are processed by OPP volunteers, since we do not have a shelter facility we check references and meet with you in your home to discuss the pet you are interested in adopting. The adoption fee for all OPP dogs/puppies is $200 which includes vaccinations, dewormer, flea/tick treatment and spay/neuter surgery - and in many cases we've treated the pet for much more if it arrives to OPP ill or injured. Our adoption fee helps cover to cover some of these costs - adopters are welcome to make an additional donation to the program at the time of adoption so we can continue to help other unwanted pets on Pine Ridge.

Visit us on Facebook to learn more about our work facebook.com/OglalaPetProject Thank you for choosing to adopt a rescued animal!

animal.description:
Have you met Chi Chi?

Chi Chi was surrendered to the San Diego Humane Society, because her family couldn't afford her

care. She is one of our younger Frosted Faces at only 7 years old, and she weighs 7 lbs.

Shortly after Chi Chi became a Frosted Face, she spent some time in a Foster home.

Chi Chi

shared

her Foster home with
t
hree other dogs and got along with all of them

.

Her Foster Mom says Chi Chi loves to snuggle, soak up the sun, and follow her all around the house! She started playing with toys while she was there, too!

Back at Frosted Faces, Chi Chi is loved by our volunteers for her sweet nature and for being a cuddle bug! She can often be found hanging out with one or two of her Frosted Friends on a bed.

Chi Chi would love a home of her own! Could it be with you? Apply to meet this precious girl: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

animal.description: The photo session in the bark park shared with 10-month-old Ludwig revealed an amazingly talented canine with a seemingly endless inventory of surprising skills. He has a quiet, attentive nature and despite his athletic stature, is a very gentle creature. He proudly performs an instantaneous sit, both on request and at his own discretion. You will find it hard to follow his motion as he shifts from a stand into a sit so quickly that it seems to materialize via teleportation. Ludwig has great eye/mouth coordination as he catches virtually all treats tossed in his general direction. A few of them were blown by the gusting wind beyond his reach and he would “hunt” them down with great delight. His joyful, energetic play was galvanizingly entertaining and awe inspiring. He was respectfully awarded his name as his elation stirred the memory of Beethoven’s interpretation of the “Ode to Joy”. (Ludwig is also celebrating the 250th anniversary of the birth of his favorite musician). As the photographer turned away to reposition for the next shot, Ludwig would silently appear behind him and give the human’s hand a tender touch with his nose just to let him know that he was going to be there, and you were the total focus of his attention. With a name like Ludwig, you know he has to be good.

Apply to meet this Puppy Mill Rescue Team dog here:  https://puppymillrescueteam.org/dog-adoption-application/

If you have a soft spot for seniors, Roxi is your girl!  At 9 years old Roxi is still young at heart. She loves going for daily strolls and playing with stuffed toys. She is completely house trained and great in the car. Although she is picky about her dog friends, she hasn’t met a person she doesn’t like. Her dream is to have a a loving family, warm bed, and plenty of treats! She has the typical goofy boxer attitude.





----------------------------------------------------
https://puppymillrescueteam.org/dog-adoption-application/


This dog is located in Rochester NY.  Applications for this dog will be considered within a 60 mile radius

When the application has been reviewed their foster will be in touch!  Make sure to check your spam email, it will be coming from a fosters personal email address.


Puppy Mill Rescue Team New York State registration No. is RR400 as we are a registered 501c3 nonprofit organization. We rescue discarded dogs and puppies from puppy mills and place them with ethical rescues that will care for their veterinary needs, house them in volunteer foster homes, and eventually adopt them into loving families. The PMRT also works to educate the public about puppy mills and supports efforts to eradicate the existence of the inhumane mass dog breeding facilities commonly known as puppy mills. The PMRT promotes choosing pet adoption, over purchasing online or from a pet store, as the vast majority of those are sourced by puppy mills.

animal.description:
** please note cupcake should be adopted into a home as an only dog, a household with kids and cats is not recommended and she should be adopted into a home where owner has experiences with her breed**

Meet  Cupcake! This one is perfect!
Cupcake is a female approximately 5 to 6 years old 44 pound English bulldog. She was previously from a breeder, and did have several litters by C-section.
Cupcake loves people, and she does OK walking on a leash, and knows to go potty outside most of the time.She is a sweet and loving girl and is ready for a home of her own.

Cupcake also has had bloodwork and dental done recently! Yay!

Interested in becoming a forever home for Cupcake? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Cupcake.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Cupcake the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  
For immediate consideration, please attach your application to the initial inquiry to help us expedite the process.

Our adoption fee is $475. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
This is Roxie!

Roxie was brought into the Orange County Shelter as a stray. She had a microchip, but no owner was found, so we made Roxie a Frosted Face on November 24th. She is 10 years old, weighs 11 lbs., and is blind. Roxie is incredibly sweet, loves to be held, and gives little kisses. She is good with other dogs and cats, too!

Roxie's sweetness may be why a two-week Frosted Fling turned into a Foster home! Roxie's Foster Mom has taken care of her as she has recovered from several surgeries: dental surgery to remove 15 teet and repair an oronasal fistula, spay, mammary masses removed, and hernia repairs. According to her Foster Mom, Roxie is a new woman! She eats comfortably now and walks 2-3 miles easily with pep in her step! More good news: the biopsy results from the mammary masses came back benign! Little Roxie is ready to find her forever family!

Her Foster Mom shares, "Roxie is the absolute sweetest little baby girl! She needs time to figure out her new space and feel relaxed, but she absolutely will relax and will be the best little companion. She is blind after all, so it's only reasonable to give a girl some time to map out the place. Here's a few other things I've learned about her:

-She sleeps through the night like sleeping beauty. She sleeps on a dog bed in my room and once she's all tucked in she'll sleep for at least 8 hours easy. No accidents through the night either!

-I've left her home alone in a crate and given free roam. Had no issues leaving her in an area free to roam, she just sleeps.

-LOVES food, and it's kind of hilarious to watch because she's so tiny!

-Loves her person and will wiggle uncontrollably anytime you go pet her! She also very much enjoys being held like a baby. She is going to be someone's perfect little baby girl."

Might Roxie be your little girl? Apply to meet her: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

Updated: 1/27/21 KG

animal.description:
Bella is in a foster home, and is currently not at the shelter. Please find info below on how to adopt her, thanks.



Homebody seeks homebody: Bella is the most loving, gentle dog with all humans. One of her favorite activities is snuggling on the couch. When you pet her, she makes happy little grunts. Talk sweetly to her, and she wiggles from her nose to her tail.



Bella has great manners inside the home: She won't chew your stuff or steal food, and she rarely barks.



Bella is not a fan of other dogs. She is working on staying calmer when she sees other dogs outside, but she will never have doggie friends.



For this reason, Bella needs to live in a single-family home with a securely fenced yard, ideally in a quiet neighborhood.



Bella also needs an experienced, patient guardian who is committed to continuing her training. While she is good with children, she requires an adult handler due to her dog reactivity. No cats or critters, please-they are too much fun to chase!



Bella would be a wonderful, easy companion for someone who works from home and is content to exercise her mostly in the yard. Even though she's still young (2-4 years old), Bella needs only moderate exercise.



HOW TO ADOPT - Please fill out a Dog Adoption Application, available at http://www.seattle.gov/animalshelter/forms.htm and email it to the Seattle Animal Shelter Foster Dog Program at adoptionreview@gmail.com.



IMPORTANT NOTE: Many of our dogs will receive numerous applications, and the Seattle Animal Shelter asks for your patience during the process of finding the very best match. If you have questions about this dog that have not been answered above, please contact us at sasfosterdogs@gmail.com. If you would like to arrange to meet this dog, you must submit an adoption application. Thank you!

Rain will remain with her family until she can be placed in an appropriate home that fits her needs! She is not for a first time dog owner.  Here is what her current owner has to say about her!
1. DEAF/doesn’t respond to most correction.  Rain really needs someone with time and patience to work with her. Very high prey drive, once locked onto a target she’s difficult to distract. 2. Likes to choose to ignore commands but has the drive to learn  3. Very hand shy (has never been hit in our home, we are unsure about her previous home.  She doesn’t like brooms or fast hand movements. Hates the vacuum) 4. Slight food guarding with other dog in the house. Never showed any reactivity towards person taking food away though 5. Absolutely NO CATS as her prey drive is very high. No young kids. (13+ fine) 7. No small dogs or small livestock such as rabbits, chickens etc.  8. Possibly ok with large dog (lived with large male GSD and did fine, but has very alpha personality so would depend on other dog) 9. Loves to play with big dogs she likes but can get a bit intense and seem aggressive in her play style. 10. Will fence fight relentlessly (always checks to see if other dog is there when let outside) 11. Digs a lot when she’s bored (needs secure yard/plenty of activities. I think she would highly benefit as a companion animal as she thrives off of being with her people) 12. Chews/shreds things heavily when bored (ex. Chewed food bowl, backyard hose, chair legs, shredded blanket in kennel... etc) 13. Weird about going through doors.  14. Knows how to sit with hand signal or for food/treats 15. Needs to learn leash manners, (she has close to none) Wants to be head of the “pack” and pulls horribly. 16. Leash reactive with other dogs (sometimes once let off leash she’s fine. It depends) 17. Very calm and well-mannered when indoors as long as she has people around. 18. Frantic when crated initially, but will calm down and curl up to sleep eventually. (A toy to chew helps her calm down) 19. Loves car rides but does better restrained because she wants to “help” you drive 20. LOVES water/snow 21. Has occasionally peed indoors to mark her territory, otherwise completely house trained. 22. Is used to being crated at night, but will also happily sleep inside on a bed. 23. Really likes carrots/ enjoys whole large carrot to chew 24. Enjoys hard chew toys/hooves/antlers. (Good way to keep her happy and entertained when she can’t be supervised so she doesn’t chew other things)
 Please research POSITIVE training techniques before applying to adopt. We care very much about your application answers and they are reviewed for completeness and the best match.   Please fill out an application on the included link: https://threerivershs.org/adoption-app-2/

The adoption fee of $125 includes spay/neuter, current vaccines, microchip, free vet visit, 30 days of pet health insurance, puppy book, and engraved ID tag.

animal.description:
I'm Jack but they call me Jack Jack sometimes. I absolutely love people and other dogs are exciting, too! Cats are kind of scary so I think I'd rather leave them be. I love playing with other dogs and then getting pets from people. If I see a tennis ball being thrown, I'm ready to go get it! Tug of war is turning out to be a fun game, too. I have yet to meet a human, dog, or toy I don't like. I'm all about fun and playing and enjoying life. 
          The shelter is not my forever home so I'm camping out here until my perfect family comes along. I love kongs and bones to chew on. I'm doing pretty well on the leash, too. I'm such a friendly guy when it comes to other dogs because I want to be friends with everyone. 
          I'm a spry 2 years old and 55 lbs. I think I am catching on to the house and kennel training part but the shelter is not the best place for me to practice because nothing beats a home with friends and love. Although the shelter is not my forever home, I'm keeping my spirits up because I know my family is out there and it's just about being patient waiting for them to find me. If you're looking for a fun and friendly guy to experience life with or maybe your dog wants a playmate, too, come visit me at the shelter and bring your dog if you have one and I'll show you my sparkling personality!

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Daisy!
I looooove to cuddle with anyone who wants to! The closer the better! I love being outside, especially if you are going to play with me. I love to play catch with balls and snowballs! My foster mommy will throw a handful of snow in the air and I love to run through it! Every time I catch that snow I get the zoomies and run around the yard as fast as I can!!! She always claps for me, which makes me go faster!!! 
I love to stand or sit on the chair in the living room and make sure my backyard is safe from intruders. I'm pretty good at the neighborhood watch gig!
I also love when my foster kids play tug with me. It's one of my favorite things to do!!!!! I also love to find those silly squeaker in stuffies. They don't last long, but it seems every time my humans run an errand, they pick up 1 or 2 more for me to destroy. 
I don't love my kennel, but I go in like a good girl when my humans have to go to work. I mean, they need to make some money to buy me all those stuffies. When they come home I am waiting patiently for them to let me out. I never bark.
I'm a really good girl looking for a ""fur""ever home with a family who loves to play and cuddle.
Sincerely, 
Daisy (AKA: Daisy-roo, Daisy-doo, Daisy Dukes, Pretty Girl)

animal.description:
Petunia is an 8 year old 17 lb. Lhasa Apso/Poodle Mix who was found wandering the streets of Mexico. We believe she was abandoned by her previous owners because of her vision loss. She has cataracts in both eyes, so she is vision impaired.

When Petunia was found she was terrified, cold, and did not eat or drink for several days. If she had not been rescued Petunia would have died from starvation. After a few months of TLC  she was later transported to  Los Angeles so she could have a better chance at finding a loving forever home. 

Petunia is a couch potato and enjoys lounging around the house. She likes to be held and going out for short walks. Petunia gets along with other dogs and keeps to herself. She would be best suited in any home with a quiet, less active lifestyle. Petunia is microchipped, vaccinated, and spayed.

If you are interested in Petunia, please complete the on-line application that can be found on our website: www.adoptmerecue.org or contact us for more information.

LOCAL ADOPTION ONLY.

Theo was brought in as a stray by animal control. He was picked up on Cheraw Hwy in Society Hill. He is very affectionate and sweet: Hw-; 43lbs; 1-2 yrs old; bull mix; 11/19/2018

Theo (now Axle) was returned 11/2020. Axle needs a home with no small animals or cats. 

Axle is a great dog. Axle knows how to sit and stay. He crates very well and walks nicely on a leash. He LOVES children of all ages and plays well with small children. He has no issue with older/bigger dogs. He has no food aggression. He has been an indoor dog since being adopted in 2018 other than going outside for playtime and potty breaks.  He is housebroken, but if left alone for an extended amount of time, he may have an accident, as would any dog. He has a fluffy chair that he lays in often, and we have fixed it up in his kennel for him. He seems confused and sad. 

He is neutered, microchipped, housebroken, and used to being in a home with a family. 

Axle would be happiest in a home with no small animals, or access to small animals.

He is an extremely well mannered dog. He knows how to sit, walks on a leash, and is very affectionate.

Meet ELLA! She is up for adoption in Texas and is an honorary Lab. ? 

She is a petite girl, only weighing about 30 lbs at nine months old! Ella can be a bit shy and submissive when meeting new people and dogs but within minutes she will be your very best friend. 

She would do best in a home with older kids 15+ years old because of her tendency to be more on the nervous side. 

She currently lives in a home with four other dogs and she loves every minute of it! Her ideal home would have at least one other confident dog for her to feed off and to mentor her on how to dog. Her foster takes her to work several times a week and she is a great office dog but is also great in a crate if she has to stay home!

Ella is crate trained and potty trained. She is spayed, microchipped, and fully vaccinated. 

Please fill out an application if you think she sounds like a great fit for you at www.luckylabrescue.com

animal.description:
Available for adoption in New England/East Coast: meet MASON!

He is about two-years-old and weighs about 60lbs. We think he might be a Lab-Boxer mix.

Mason loves to be pet and shake. He would do well in a home where he can get lots of exercise and activity. He's lived in a home with another dog (littermate) since he was born, but they started not getting along.  Which can happen when two puppies stay together. 

We think for now Mason would do better in a home without adults and or adults and older teens without other dogs, he needs a bit of proper socializing in the doggo department. 

He'd do better in a home with a tall fence (he's a jumper) versus an apartment or condo, he will bark when he hears noises or someone pulls up. 

Mason does best crated when home alone.  He should be supervised in any new setting as he sometimes likes to sneak off and chew things he's not supposed to.  We think in the right home when he's getting the right amount of exercise he will grow into a good boy. 

He is neutered, vaccinated, housebroken, and microchipped. 

If you are interested in adopting, please go to www.luckylabrescue.com and complete an adoption application.

Location: New Orleans, Louisiana 

Sonny was a owner surrender to Cane Haven Rescue with his brother Brody. We wanted to give them another chance at life. They are approximately 7-8 months old, up to date on vaccinations, neutered & microchipped. 

Sonny is just your typical 7-8 month old pup. He loves exploring new things, learning new tricks and showing his humans how good of a boy he is. He was apart of a litter that was unexpected and there was a plea to save the entire litter before the shelter was involved. We stepped right up to save these handsome fellas! 

Sonny is house trained, kennel trained & knows his basic commands/manners. 

Interested adopters can fill out an application at canehavenrescue.com. 
Any possible questions about Sonny, please email canehavenrescue@gmail.com 

Cane Haven Rescue will transport any of their adoptable dogs to the right home. We do require adoption fees that are based on the age & health status of the adoptable dog. The adoption fee covers every single dog in CHR with vaccinations, heartworm test, deworming, microchip, spay/neuter & medications. All CHR adoptable dogs are current on their monthly  heartworm and flea medication. A CHR representative will do a home check to ensure the pets are placed in a secure and loving home. 

www.canehavenrescue.com

animal.description:
Peaches is 5 yrs young and 140 lbs. She came from her one and only home where she was much loved, integrated with all sizes of other dogs, children of all sizes and ages and cats. She is a mild-mannered very dear big girl.

Please find our applications and valuable information under "Adopt a dog"* on our website: *www.beaglesandbuddies.com* and email your application to beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Let us know your preference of appointment day/time and which dogs you are interested in and we will do our best to accommodate and email you the closest appointment available. Please allow us up to a week to get back to you. Most appointments will be Friday-Sunday, 10 am - 2 pm, for an hour.

*Note bring any other dog/s and the entire family to your meet and greet at B&B.* A complimentary training manual is included with each adoption, authored by terristeuben.com. Check out her website - she is fabulous!

B&B is glad to be open during the pandemic. We know the value and comfort of a loving pet companion and are doing our best to help the dogs and folks who need them. We update our website daily and are always rescuing, vetting, rehabilitating, socializing.

* We are accepting applications for volunteers to spend time with our dogs, hang out, sing/read to the shy ones, walk/toss ball with those who go to the playgrounds; cleaning, office work, gardening, and building/repair projects! *
Are you my furrever family?

For further info on the adoption process, please visit our home page and check out the "Adopt a Dog" section, which has thorough instructions. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and

fully vaccinated before adoption; they have been wormed, bathed, socialized, walked daily and much loved; each adoptee leaves with a leash, collar, and all medical records.

Our prices are higher than the shelters' because we nurse the dogs through their illnesses and get them needed surgeries and dentals. We also spend time socializing. Furthermore, unlike shelters, rescues do not get financial aid from the government and must rely on donations, grants, and adoption fees. Our fees for adults start at $150 and go up to $750. The higher end is for our most in demand dogs, such as young beagles and other purebred dogs. The lower end is for dogs who have been here a while. For puppies, we may go beyond this and charge $1000. The good news is that, because rescues fall under the "charity" category, the fees for our dogs are officially donations and are therefore tax deductible. You can think of it as donating to a worthy cause and getting a dog in return!

Sponsor Me

Beagles & Buddies must find ways to raise money so we can continue saving dogs. Your tax-deductible donation keeps our rescue kennel operating!

Hours

Friday: 10 am to 3 pm

Saturday: 10 am to 3 pm

Sunday: 10 am to 3 pm

Monday: CLOSED

Tuesday: CLOSED

Wednesday: CLOSED

Thursday: CLOSED



Weekday appointments may be available. We are a small staff and do our best to accommodate your needs. **Note that during COVID, we are not holding open houses on any day. Please email us for an appointment and include your application (found on our website, beaglesandbuddies.com, under "Forms"). Most appointments will be Friday through Sunday, though other days may also be available. We usually schedule one appointment per hour. Allow 1-2 hours for your appointment. Please look at our website and make a list of one or more dogs that you would like to see.

Contacting Us

If you have a question about adopting, giving up a dog, boarding, or volunteering, please visit the appropriate tabs on our
home page.

For more specific questions, call 626-444-9664 (please leave a voicemail if no answer) or email at beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Note that
Emailing
is always preferred!

Thanks!

Please note: If you are viewing this profile anywhere other than Beagles & Buddies own website, you are not receiving full info. Visit info on pet here.

animal.description:
Meet Jezabel, our precious and affectionate Malinois mix who is approximately three years old. The first thing you need to know about Jezabel, she loves her people, even more than treats often. She is very affectionate towards her people and will sing and dance (bark on her back legs) to welcome you back home in excitement. She seems to more independent, so she should be the only dog in the house, but she will also help make sure that no squirrels or other rodents have taken residence in your yard. She enjoys walks, but she does pull on the leash in order to get her nose to all of those good smells. She is ready to be in a home where she can bond with her human and show how good of a companion she could be. If you are interested in Jezabel, please fill out an application on our website or call us in the office M-Th between 10am-4pm to discuss her further. 

Please note that Jezabel has been diagnosed with moderate to severe hip dysplasia. At the shelter, she has been receiving Adequan shots to microscopically build her cartilage back up. There are three more shots in this series and they will be provided with the adoption. She has also been receiving Underwater Therapy at Sierra Vet Specialists while performing rehab tasks everyday at the shelter. She has three more sessions at SVS and these are also included in the adoption price. Since her rehab efforts have begun, the vet noted that Jezabel's range of motion has increased, her muscle mass has increased, and she is less guarding of her legs. The daily rehab efforts will need to be continued in the home, but are also a great source of exercise, mentally and physically, for Jezabel. Jezabel enjoys walks, but her hips do get more sore if she pulls a lot on a walk, so she may need help learning how to be a better leash companion. This was accomplished in her foster home a year ago, but she has forgotten a little.
